item.description: Texture Missing When a texture is missing from an object a shader will typically resort to rendering it in one colour, in the example below, pink, to signify an issue. Texture Corruption A texture may render incorrectly/become corrupte for various reasons, for example, offsets incorrectly set, the UV map is incorrect or other shader related issues. Similar visually jaring effects may also be due to lighting problems.
